cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) using neural models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses bidirectional LSTMs and conditional random fields, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with subword units, which are related to character-level and byte-level representations, which are common in computer vision (CV) and natural language generation (NLG). Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also possible sub-categories.
